column5: 1st Bill. Here are your #20 ants and midges  Added indicators to some so they can be seen,,,,,,,,,,,,,,   Terry, your trebles you have been hounding me for,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,   Yours are coming Scott,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
Well that looks like some pretty nice work.  No idle hands at your desk.
Funny thing about tying those small baits.  I was getting a cramp in my right leg . . LOL I have #22 on hand. They are NEXT,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,Once I recover.LOL
Now ya talkin'! #20's in that pattern was my go to, except tied on barbless spade hooks. They were a much finer gauge wire. In those days #16's were large hooks and 18's were average.
Those are the ones with no eye correct ? Just use a slip knot to change fly's ?  Watched a video of a guy from over the pond use these hooks . Very cool .
Could you tie a few of these for me  Merry Christmas

Bet I could,but I wont.LOL I just tied up 50 dries for a customer this morning . Now I am off to prep the roast of beast and veggies for dinner .  Back at ya bud. Did ya go for a sled ride this morning ?
nice handiwork! You should start making musky lures though...that is where the $$$ is at
To bad. Roads were prime at 4 am this morning . LOL
I was up at five and the buggers  had already  plowed my road or I would have go for a rip
